Sentencas: The cobaltate perovskites Sr1-xDyxCoO3- (SDCO, x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) materials were synthesized and evaluated as cathode for La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3- solid electrolyte supported intermediate-temperature-solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Characterization of Sr1-xDyxCoO3-δ (x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) Cathode Materials for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The crystal structure of Sr0.9Dy0.1CoO3- was defined in the cubic Pm-3m space group (No. 221), Sr0.8Dy0.2CoO3- and Sr0.7Dy0.3CoO3- had a tetragonal I4/mmm structure.
Titulo: Characterization of Sr1-xDyxCoO3-δ (x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) Cathode Materials for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The electrical conductivities were all higher than 100Scm(-1) in the temperature of 170-800 degrees C.
Titulo: Characterization of Sr1-xDyxCoO3-δ (x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) Cathode Materials for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The polarization resistance (R-p) and its activation energy (E-a) increased with increasing x. SEM analysis confirmed the porous microstructure of the SDCO cathodes and good LSGM|LDC|SDCO adherence.
Titulo: Characterization of Sr1-xDyxCoO3-δ (x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) Cathode Materials for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Sr0.9Dy0.1CoO3- exhibited the best cathode characteristics with a maximum test-cell power density of 841mWcm(-2), being a high potential candidate of cathode material for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Characterization of Sr1-xDyxCoO3-δ (x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) Cathode Materials for IT-SOFCs
